# Deployment

This prototype is hosted on [VibeSharing](https://vibesharing.app) with a GitHub-to-Vercel pipeline.

## How to deploy

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Describe what changed"
git push origin main
```

Vercel auto-deploys from this repository on every push to `main`.

## Deploy rules

- Do **not** run `vercel`, `vercel --yes`, or `vercel deploy` from the CLI
- Do **not** zip files or use a deploy API
- Do **not** create new Vercel projects manually
- Deploy **only** by pushing to this git repository

## Project structure (Vite + React)

- `index.html` — Vite entry (root)
- `src/` — application source (`App.tsx`, `src/pages/`, `src/components/`, …)
- `public/` — static assets (served as-is at URL root)

Vite is not Next.js: there is no `app/` directory. The main UI lives under `src/`; static files belong in `public/`.

## Build

Production build: `pnpm install` then `pnpm run build` (output in `dist/`). The hosting platform runs this on deploy.
